{"comments":"Dynamic viscosity database in Pa·s (Pascal-seconds).\n\n## What is Viscosity?\n\nDynamic viscosity (μ) measures a fluid's resistance to flow.\nSI unit: Pa·s (Pascal-seconds) = kg/(m·s)\nCommon unit: cP (centipoise) = 0.001 Pa·s\n\nNewton's law: τ = μ × (du/dy)\n(shear stress = viscosity × velocity gradient)\n\n## Physical Bounds\n\n- **Minimum**: ~0.000001 Pa·s (superfluid helium approaches 0)\n- **Maximum**: ~10^12 Pa·s (pitch, glass)\n- **Common range**: 0.0001 - 10000 Pa·s\n\n## Why This Matters\n\nAt billion-agent scale, viscosity determines:\n- Fluid simulation behavior (how liquids pour, drip, spread)\n- Haptic feedback for fluid interaction (stirring honey vs water)\n- Material state transitions (melting, freezing, thickening)\n- Rendering (droplet shapes, surface waves, splashing)\n\n## Related Papers\n\n- Stream Function Solver (divergence-free fluid simulation)\n- Fire-X (multi-phase combustion with viscous fluids)\n\n## Data Sources\n\nCRC Handbook, engineering toolbox, food science literature.\nAll values at 20-25°C unless noted. Temperature significantly affects viscosity.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Fluid","Viscosity"],"DynamicViscosity"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[178,58],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/Viscosity.purs","start":[178,1]},"title":"eqDynamicViscosity"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Fluid","Viscosity"],"DynamicViscosity"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[179,60],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/Viscosity.purs","start":[179,1]},"title":"ordDynamicViscosity"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Fluid","Viscosity"],"DynamicViscosity"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[182,65],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/Viscosity.purs","start":[181,1]},"title":"showDynamicViscosity"}],"comments":"Dynamic viscosity in Pa·s [0.000001, 10000000000.0].\n\n## Bounds Rationale\n\n- Lower bound 0.000001: Below superfluid helium\n- Upper bound 10^10: Above pitch/glass (10^9 Pa·s)\n\nHigher viscosity = more resistance to flow = thicker feeling.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[176,51],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/Viscosity.purs","start":[176,1]},"title":"DynamicViscosity"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create DynamicViscosity with validation.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Maybe"],"Maybe"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Fluid","Viscosity"],"DynamicViscosity"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[185,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/Viscosity.purs","start":[185,1]},"title":"viscosity"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create DynamicViscosity with clamping.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation